{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 23,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 23 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:1",
      "text": "If thou sit to sup at the table of a prince, consider attentively the things set before thee:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:2",
      "text": "and apply thine hand, knowing that it behoves thee to prepare such meats: but if thou art very insatiable,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:3",
      "text": "desire not his provisions; for these belong to a false life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:4",
      "text": "If thou art poor, measure not thyself with a rich man; but refrain thyself in thy wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:5",
      "text": "If thou shouldest fix thine eye upon him, he will disappear; for wings like an eagle’s are prepared for him, and he returns to the house of his master.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:6",
      "text": "Sup not with an envious man, neither desire thou his meats:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:7",
      "text": "so he eats and drinks as if any one should swallow a hair, and do not bring him in to thyself, nor eat thy morsel with him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:8",
      "text": "for he will vomit it up, and spoil thy fair words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:9",
      "text": "Say nothing in the ears of a fool, lest at any time he sneer at thy wise words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:10",
      "text": "Remove not the ancient landmarks; and enter not upon the possession of the fatherless:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:11",
      "text": "for the Lord is their redeemer; he is mighty, and will plead their cause with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:12",
      "text": "Apply thine heart to instruction, and prepare thine ears for words of discretion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:13",
      "text": "Refrain not from chastening a child; for if thou beat him with the rod, he shall not die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:14",
      "text": "For thou shalt beat him with the rod, and shalt deliver his soul from death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:15",
      "text": "Son, if thy heart be wise, thou shalt also gladden my heart;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:16",
      "text": "and thy lips shall converse with my lips, if they be right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:17",
      "text": "Let not thine heart envy sinners: but be thou in the fear of the Lord all the day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:18",
      "text": "For if thou shouldest keep these things, thou shalt have posterity; and thine hope shall not be removed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:19",
      "text": "Hear, my son, and be wise, and rightly direct the thoughts of thine heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:20",
      "text": "Be not a wine-bibber, neither continue long at feasts, and purchases of flesh:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:21",
      "text": "for every drunkard and whoremonger shall be poor; and every sluggard shall clothe himself with tatters and ragged garments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:22",
      "text": "Hearken, my son, to thy father which begot thee, and despise not thy mother because she is grown old.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:23",
      "text": "A righteous father brings up his children well; and his soul rejoices over a wise son.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:25",
      "text": "Let thy father and thy mother rejoice over thee, and let her that bore thee be glad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:26",
      "text": "My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:27",
      "text": "For a strange house is a vessel full of holes; and a strange well is narrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:28",
      "text": "For such a one shall perish suddenly; and every transgressor shall be cut off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:29",
      "text": "Who has woe? who trouble? who has quarrels? and who vexations and disputes? who has bruises without a cause? whose eyes are livid?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:30",
      "text": "Are not those of them that stay long at wine? are not those of them that haunt the places where banquets are? Be not drunk with wine; but converse with just men, and converse with them openly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:31",
      "text": "For if thou shouldest set thine eyes on bowls and cups, thou shalt afterwards go more naked than a pestle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:32",
      "text": "But at last such a one stretches himself out as one smitten by a serpent, and venom is diffused through him as by a horned serpent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:33",
      "text": "Whenever thine eyes shall behold a strange woman, then thy mouth shall speak perverse things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.34",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:34",
      "text": "And thou shalt lie as in the midst of the sea, and as a pilot in a great storm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:proverbs.23.35",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 23,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 23:35",
      "text": "And thou shalt say, They smote me, and I was not pained; and they mocked me, and I knew it not: when will it be morning, that I may go and seek those with whom I may go in company?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
